cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to predict the evolution of words. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses supervised learning algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of historical frequencies of words and the Google Books Ngram Corpus suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also uses features based on a word's length and characters, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the evolution of language, which could also fall under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
